<br>
Now, other things, those damn spiders in Velketor's can be soloed a LOT easier with the epic effect.  I've also taken up re-visiting the old zones I used to use when lower level, soloed through all of Unrest, Mistmoore, and Dalnir so far just for fun.  The mana regen lowers our downtime, and it's a blast going back to these zones, giving out items you pick up from doing this to very happy people.<br>
<br>
Then, there's the added benefit of being able to melee unbuffed with it upwards of 40 points of damage.  Most out there don't mention this, but one of the greatest ways to save mana is to melee a bit once the mobs are low on health.  You can't do this in real XP camps, but how many times have you gotten annoyed because greenies force you to waste mana?  Well, when you hit for 40+ damage melee, and have the &quot;free&quot; 800HP from the effect, you CAN cut many mobs down with one nuke, then melee it the rest of the way.  It's little things like this that just add to the fun of playing again.<br>
<br>
  XP doesn't mean much when you know level 60 is the highest level, and you get to level 59 and 60 in my opinion, it's not like there's a RUSH to get to 60, unless you are in an uberguild that pushes you to get to 60 just for banes.  Because of this, PLAY with your epic, do things you'd never think about doing.  I'm currently at 115 strength unbuffed, and I'm meleeing for 43 damage.  When in a camp, ask for a haste buff, and go up and start beating on the mobs, just for fun, or get into melee only duels with non-melee classes unbuffed(this also works if you have a brawlstick).  After all the grief it takes to get the epic, go out, and have fun with it, because you've earned it.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 59 Wizard<br>
Bloodguard of Souls<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
